Put a large #saucepan{} of water with a good pinch of @salt{pinch} on to boil for the wheat pasta. Cut the @broccoli{1/2}(cut into small florets) into small florets (like small little trees!). Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1%large}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Roughly chop the @chives{1}(roughly chopped). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest the @lemon{1/2}(zested then cut into wedges) then cut into wedges. Halve the @red chilli{1/2}(halved lengthways, deseeded and finely chopped) lengthways, deseed then finely chop.

Add the @spaghetti{200%g} to your pan of boiling water and cook for ~{11%minutes}. Once done, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan (off the heat). Toss with a little @olive oil{} to stop it sticking together.

Whilst your wheat pasta cooks, put a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @olive oil{} drizzled with a pinch of salt and a grind of @black pepper{}. Once hot, add the broccoli, a pinch of salt and a grind of pepper. Add a splash of @water{150%ml} and pop a lid on the pan. Cook until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}, then remove the lid and continue frying until the broccoli is a little brown and crispy round the edges, stirring occasionally, ~{2-3%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{} and cover with #foil{} to keep warm.

Lower the heat to medium and add another drizzle of @olive oil{} to the now empty frying pan (no need to wash). Add the shallot and cook until slightly softened, ~{4%minutes}. Add the garlic, lemon zest and a pinch of chilli (add less chilli if you don't like heat). Cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Add the @vegetable stock powder{1/2%tsp} to the pan along with the water. Bring to the boil and stir to dissolve the stock powder. Simmer for ~{2%minutes}, then stir in the @creme fraiche{112.5%ml} and @hot smoked salmon{99%g}(flaked). Add a good grind of pepper and bring to the boil again. Lower the heat and simmer until the salmon is piping hot, stirring occasionally, ~{2%minutes}.

Squeeze in half the lemon juice, taste to check for seasoning, then return the broccoli to the pan. Stir gently then take off the heat. Combine with the wheat spaghetti and serve in #bowls{} with the remaining lemon wedges on the side and the chives sprinkled on top. Sprinkle over a little more chilli if you like heat. Enjoy!

> We're thinking pink today. Salmon pink. Not only is this fish delicious, it's packed to the gills with omega 3 fatty acids which have been shown to have benefits for both brain function and blood pressure. So dinner can be good for the head and the heart - and the taste buds of course. Enjoy!